# Exclusions — always-skip rules   (OPTIONAL)
#
# Copy to context/exclusions.md to hard-filter contacts and companies before they
# cost you any enrichment credits. These are applied as a deterministic gate, not
# a score — anything matching is dropped (stage = skipped), never enriched.

## Always-skip titles
# Title keywords that disqualify a contact regardless of company fit.
[intern, student, trainee, apprentice, "working student", "werkstudent", retired, freelance]

## Always-skip company types
# Company categories you never sell to.
[<e.g. staffing agency, recruiting firm, "lead generation", reseller, competitor>]

## Exclude specific domains / companies
# Exact accounts to never contact (current customers, partners, do-not-contact).
[<example.com>, <competitor.com>]

## Notes
# - Exclusions run BEFORE qualification and enrichment, so they protect your spend.
# - For cross-campaign "already contacted / bounced / unsubscribed" suppression,
#   enable the Postgres master-dedup backend (storage/postgres/master-optional.sql);
#   the local backend has no cross-campaign memory.
